name: Hommonculus
description:
Thirty-five (35) liters of water.
Twenty (20) kilograms of carbon.
Four (4) liters of ammonia.
One point five (1.5) kilograms of lime.
Eight hundred (800) grams of phosphorus.
Two hundred and fifty (250) grams of salt.
One hundred (100) grams of saltpeter.
Eighty (80) grams of sulfur.
Seven point five (7.5) grams of fluorine.
Five (5) grams of iron.
Three (3) grams of silicon.
Fifteen (15) other trace elements, in their exact measurements (if you can find those measurements).
Any human/animal/plant/mythical DNA.
One (1) giant development tube.
One (1) Sorcerer's stone (also known as a Philosopher's stone).
Ten thousand volts (10,000) worth of electricity.
